HTML :
<div class="modal"> → Hidden popup container
<p>Modal Content</p> → Text inside the modal
<button class="open-modal"> → Button to open
<button class="close-modal"> → Button to close

CSS :
position: fixed; → Keeps the modal centered
visibility: hidden; → Hides modal initially
opacity: 0; → Starts invisible, gradually becomes visible

JavaScript: 
document.querySelector(".open-modal") → Finds the button
modal.classList.add("show") → Displays the modal
modal.classList.remove("show") → Hides the modal
eventListener("click", closeModal) → Closes when clicked outside
